/**
 * A CDS tranche product representing a slice of a CDS index portfolio.
 * <p>
 * A CDS tranche is defined by attachment and detachment points on the loss distribution
 * of the underlying CDS index. It represents synthetic CDO (Collateralized Debt Obligation)
 * tranche exposure.
 * <p>
 * The attachment point defines the lower bound and the detachment point defines the upper bound
 * of the tranche's exposure to portfolio losses, expressed as fractions of the notional (0.0-1.0).
